In a speech at a private residence in Weston, Massachusetts, President Joe Biden thanked his supporters and emphasized the importance of the upcoming 2024 election. He highlighted the threats to American democracy posed by former President Donald Trump and his supporters, noting Trump's denial of the 2020 election results and his intentions to destroy American democracy. Biden urged Americans from all political backgrounds to come together to protect democracy and prevent Trump from being reelected. He also discussed the progress made during his presidency, such as job creation, economic growth, and infrastructure investments. Biden stressed the need for unity and optimism in moving forward as a nation.